here we have a legitimate business rule that specifies a CUSTOMER can have zero, one or more ACCOUNTs and that an ACCOUNT must have at least one or more CUSTOMERs. So the business allows the concept of a join account, but for the logical model (i.e. talking business) we do not need to resolve this - in fact sometimes it's easier for the business people to read and contribute to models when left as a "many to many " relationship. However it always must be corrected in the physical model if we're doing a relational database implementation since most relational database systems don't permit foreign keys on both sides of a
